Print a clear summary:

```
proteinstack environment configured.

Backends available:
  ✓ RFdiffusion3  (<path>)
  ✗ BindCraft     (not found — install from github.com/martinpacesa/BindCraft)
  ✗ PXDesign      (not configured)

Sequence design:
  ✓ ProteinMPNN   (<path>)

Validation:
  ✓ ESMFold       (pip package)
  ✗ AlphaFold2    (not found — needed for accurate interface validation)

GPU: <CUDA available — cuda:0 (NVIDIA A100)> OR <CPU only — jobs will be slow>

Config written to: .proteinstack/config.yaml

Next: run /analyze-structure on your target PDB, then /design-binder.
```

If no backends are available: warn clearly — "No backbone generation backends found.
Install RFdiffusion3 or BindCraft before running /design-binder."

